679
00:56:35,727 --> 00:56:40,027
Look, I was talking to Nick
about the loan idea. It won't work,

680
00:56:40,499 --> 00:56:42,296
not until you're 25.

681
00:56:56,648 --> 00:56:59,446
You know the story about this mark here?

682
00:57:00,585 --> 00:57:03,110
You know it's how your parents met?

683
00:57:05,824 --> 00:57:10,227
See, your mom, she went into
this repair place to get some work done.

684
00:57:10,295 --> 00:57:12,855
And this guy, your dad,

685
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:16,729
he had this old...

686
00:57:18,737 --> 00:57:21,797
- What do you call this part right here?
- It's a scroll.

687
00:57:22,674 --> 00:57:24,107
A scroll.

688
00:57:25,577 --> 00:57:30,207
He had this old scroll that he had saved,
and he told her he could put it on.

689
00:57:32,617 --> 00:57:34,107
Hers was new.

690
00:57:39,324 --> 00:57:41,952
I don't know the rest of the details.

691
00:57:42,894 --> 00:57:45,294
I found the invoices for the job,

692
00:57:46,064 --> 00:57:49,033
the drawings,
and my dad sketched it all out.

693
00:57:52,037 --> 00:57:53,368
Excuse me.

694
00:58:00,412 --> 00:58:03,540
I guess he wanted her to know
how it would work.

695
00:58:04,816 --> 00:58:06,750
That's very detailed.

696
00:58:07,586 --> 00:58:10,419
He must have liked to plan everything out.

697
00:58:17,729 --> 00:58:20,357
Are you asking me if you can sell it?

698
00:58:28,139 --> 00:58:30,073
Listen to me.

699
00:58:30,141 --> 00:58:33,338
When they died,
I moved down here to look after you.

700
00:58:34,613 --> 00:58:36,808
I wanted to keep you here.

701
00:58:37,115 --> 00:58:38,673
I wanted to keep you in this house.

702
00:58:38,750 --> 00:58:41,981
It was also a chance
to get away from your father.

703
00:58:43,221 --> 00:58:46,486
Things are expensive here, Simon.
You should know that.

704
00:58:47,759 --> 00:58:49,624
We're still carrying the mortgage
on this place.

705
00:58:49,694 --> 00:58:51,685
You're going to be needing money
for university.

706
00:58:51,763 --> 00:58:53,822
What do you want me to do?

707
00:59:05,443 --> 00:59:07,240
Can I think about it?

708
00:59:11,449 --> 00:59:13,644
Yeah, you can think about it.

709
00:59:14,452 --> 00:59:17,182
I know it means a lot. I understand that.

710
00:59:22,394 --> 00:59:25,454
There's something
that I don't understand, Tom.

711
00:59:26,798 --> 00:59:28,663
Why would my dad
want to put a new scroll on?

712
00:59:28,733 --> 00:59:32,965
I mean, it doesn't really increase
the value of the violin.

713
00:59:33,038 --> 00:59:37,168
You could cut it right off
and it would be just as valuable, right?

714
00:59:38,343 --> 00:59:39,810
I don't know.

715
00:59:46,017 --> 00:59:50,579
There's something that my father did that
might explain his character a little better.

716
00:59:50,655 --> 00:59:53,988
When he met my mom,
he was repairing violins.

717
00:59:54,059 --> 00:59:55,720
That was his job.

718
00:59:56,595 --> 00:59:58,995
She came in with this instrument.

719
01:00:00,498 --> 01:00:03,399
Well, it's... It's a long story.

720
01:00:03,902 --> 01:00:07,167
But the last time I was saying

721
01:00:07,839 --> 01:00:10,000
that it wouldn't have mattered if my father

722
01:00:10,075 --> 01:00:11,872
had seen the other people
on board that flight.

723
01:00:11,943 --> 01:00:16,471
It wouldn't have changed his mind
if he'd recognized their humanity.

724
01:00:17,716 --> 01:00:19,343
And I realized

725
01:00:19,551 --> 01:00:21,416
that you never know when

726
01:00:21,486 --> 01:00:24,853
or how something might affect you.

727
01:00:24,923 --> 01:00:26,788
I mean, most of the times
when we find ourselves

728
01:00:26,858 --> 01:00:28,985
most affected by something

729
01:00:29,527 --> 01:00:32,291
is when we think it might be taken away.

730
01:00:33,465 --> 01:00:35,797
