01:16:28,619 --> 01:16:31,053
The first thing you need to know
is that this family knows its place,

920
01:16:31,121 --> 01:16:33,351
and its place isn't to tell me what I said
or didn't say.

921
01:16:33,424 --> 01:16:36,689
Their place isn't to sit at my table
and ask me to explain myself.

922
01:16:36,760 --> 01:16:40,821
Because the way my children were raised,
this would be considered rude.

923
01:16:42,700 --> 01:16:44,327
Do you understand that?

924
01:16:45,869 --> 01:16:50,033
Maybe it's normal for you to act this way,

925
01:16:50,441 --> 01:16:53,740
to be heated, hot-blooded, impassioned,

926
01:16:53,944 --> 01:16:58,472
rude across the family table,
but in my house this is not acceptable.

927
01:16:58,949 --> 01:17:01,645
- When Rachel's mother was alive...
- Hey, Simon.

928
01:17:01,719 --> 01:17:03,243
...she had a rule...

929
01:17:03,320 --> 01:17:06,619
- Want to go out for a ride in my truck?
...whenever anyone got angry at this table

930
01:17:06,690 --> 01:17:08,988
or anywhere...

931
01:17:09,560 --> 01:17:11,551
- Okay.
...she would nod.

932
01:17:22,539 --> 01:17:24,234
<i>- You don't talk...
- Tom.</i>

933
01:17:24,308 --> 01:17:27,072
<i>Tom, come back. Please come back now.</i>

934
01:17:27,144 --> 01:17:29,544
After she spent the whole week
making this meal,

935
01:17:29,613 --> 01:17:30,944
do you like to see her drinking?

936
01:17:31,015 --> 01:17:32,175
- You have no idea...
- No! No!

937
01:17:32,249 --> 01:17:34,740
...what you're talking about.
- You make her do this.

938
01:17:34,818 --> 01:17:36,115
She is miserable here.

939
01:17:36,186 --> 01:17:37,983
<i>You make her miserable here!</i>

940
01:17:38,055 --> 01:17:41,991
<i>Come, please come. Tom, can you hear me?</i>

941
01:17:42,059 --> 01:17:43,458
...who's civilized!
- Tom, can you hear me?

942
01:17:43,527 --> 01:17:45,154
Please, just come back!

943
01:17:46,697 --> 01:17:49,564
<i>Tom, just come back.
Please, just come back.</i>

944
01:17:49,633 --> 01:17:51,191
<i>...you don't talk!</i>

945
01:18:03,414 --> 01:18:04,972
<i>I pretended I couldn't hear,</i>

946
01:18:06,216 --> 01:18:08,411
that the connection was bad.

947
01:18:09,153 --> 01:18:11,144
And she kept calling.

948
01:18:11,855 --> 01:18:13,686
And I didn't pick up.

949
01:18:16,026 --> 01:18:17,323
Why not?

950
01:18:19,196 --> 01:18:21,756
Because someone
was finally giving it to him.

951
01:18:21,832 --> 01:18:25,598
No one had ever stood up to him
like that, confronted him like that.

952
01:18:25,669 --> 01:18:28,661
I wanted him to explode for me.

953
01:18:32,142 --> 01:18:34,474
That's what I wanted Sami to do.

954
01:18:37,147 --> 01:18:41,015
- Explode?
- Yes.

955
01:18:44,888 --> 01:18:47,618
- How long did it last?
- I don't know.

956
01:18:49,226 --> 01:18:52,423
He must have seen
that she was too drunk to drive.

957
01:18:55,632 --> 01:18:59,591
I know... I know it's not my fault.

958
01:19:01,038 --> 01:19:03,063
But it is your fault.

959
01:19:05,042 --> 01:19:07,067
You didn't answer her call for help.

960
01:19:07,144 --> 01:19:09,635
If you had driven back,
you could have taken them home.

961
01:19:09,713 --> 01:19:12,045
Sami wouldn't have had to drive.

962
01:19:16,854 --> 01:19:21,120
You have lived with this far too long
to deny your responsibility.

963
01:19:25,929 --> 01:19:28,830
When I got back it was done.
They were gone.

964
01:19:31,668 --> 01:19:35,001
I walked in, my father's screaming
that he did it on purpose.

965
01:19:35,072 --> 01:19:36,164
Okay?

966
01:19:36,640 --> 01:19:38,369
That he killed himself and Rachel.

967
01:19:38,442 --> 01:19:42,401
That he called from the car and said
he was going to kill himself and Rachel.

968
01:19:42,479 --> 01:19:44,777
- Why?
- 'Cause he was a monster.

969
01:19:46,016 --> 01:19:50,510
That's what my dad always thought,
and now there's no one to disprove him.

970
01:19:53,557 --> 01:19:54,649
Okay?

971
01:19:56,226 --> 01:19:59,923
But Sami was not a monster.

972
01:20:01,532 --> 01:20:02,624
No.

973
01:20:04,401 --> 01:20:05,629
Not him.

974
01:21:24,281 --> 01:21:27,182
How long have you known
that Simon was their child?

975
01:21:27,451 --> 01:21:30,079
The moment I was transferred to the school.

976
01:21:30,821 --> 01:21:33,187
The moment I saw his last name.

977
01:21:36,426 --> 01:21:40,726
It became my secret.

978
01:21:45,135 --> 01:21:46,727
Does Simon know?

979
01:21:48,639 --> 01:21:49,663
No.

980
01:21:56,647 --> 01:21:58,376
I watched him grow.

981
01:22:00,851 --> 01:22:04,412
I always saw him as Sami's child.

982
01:22:04,788 --> 01:22:07,757
Not the way he looks. His manner.

983
01:22:11,428 --> 01:22:17,492
These things became
much more complicated as Simon grew.

984
01:22:18,902 --> 01:22:22,565
And that's when you decided
to visit his house.

985
01:22:23,407 --> 01:22:25,136
I used to drive by.

986
01:22:26,476 --> 01:22:31,379
I would watch him inside,
playing with Simon, cooking.

987
01:22:31,448 --> 01:22:33,382
He was a great cook.

988
01:22:40,357 --> 01:22:43,884
I watched him put up
the Christmas decorations.

989
01:22:44,528 --> 01:22:47,258
That was very generous of him,

990
01:22:48,899 --> 01:22:51,367
coming from the upbringing he had.

991
01:22:58,742 --> 01:23:02,200
I'm sorry. I should have never done that,

992
01:23:02,879 --> 01:23:04,870
come to the house.

993
01:23:06,183 --> 01:23:08,208
What were you expecting to find?

994
01:23:10,220 --> 01:23:11,847
I don't know.

995
01:23:13,991 --> 01:23:15,288
I don't.

996
01:23:30,841 --> 01:23:32,399
Thanks, man.

997
01:26:25,582 --> 01:26:27,846
<i>You can sell the violin now, Tom.</i>

998
01:26:28,818 --> 01:26:30,752
<i>You have my permission.</i>

999
01:26:34,724 --> 01:26:37,887
<i>Remember when I asked you
about cutting the scroll off?</i>

1000
01:26:39,262 --> 01:26:42,857
<i>Well, it's something that I had to do.</i>

1001
01:26:43,366 --> 01:26:46,267
<i>It's kind of hard to describe why.</i>

1002
01:26:47,904 --> 01:26:51,305
<i>I don't think it'll affect the value very much</i>

1003
01:26:51,741 --> 01:26:55,040
<i>since it doesn't change the sound.</i>

1004
01:26:56,279 --> 01:26:59,180
<i>I hope it'll pay for all the things
that we'll need.</i>

1005
01:27:59,676 --> 01:28:01,871
I'm going to the Holy Land.

1006
01:28:02,512 --> 01:28:04,275
It's all the Holy Land.

1007
01:28:13,123 --> 01:28:15,250
<i>I can feel the baby kicking.</i>

1008
01:28:40,483 --> 01:28:44,146
Grandpa, I really need to know
what happened that night.

1009
01:28:45,055 --> 01:28:47,148
He was going to kill her.

1010
01:28:49,192 --> 01:28:52,889
- He called and said...
- He could have called to apologize

1011
01:28:52,962 --> 01:28:56,796
or to find out if I was back.
Or it could have been my mother.

1012
01:30:04,167 --> 01:30:06,158
Would you like to come in?

1013
01:30:07,871 --> 01:30:09,304
For coffee?

1014
01:30:12,575 --> 01:30:15,772
Must be strange
to see those wedding photographs.

1015
01:30:16,446 --> 01:30:18,539
He never said he wasn't married.

1016
01:30:18,681 --> 01:30:21,809
It's part of the reason
my dad was so suspicious of him.

1017
01:30:22,485 --> 01:30:26,888
- If he could do that to me...
- That sort of idea, yeah.

1018
01:30:28,491 --> 01:30:31,187
Except your father did not know me.

1019
01:30:31,494 --> 01:30:35,260
If he did, maybe he would understand
what Sami was running away from.

1020
01:30:35,465 --> 01:30:37,433
What do you mean?

1021
01:30:38,468 --> 01:30:42,302
- I have strange ways.
- Yes, you do.

1022
01:30:43,973 --> 01:30:46,373
You thought I was crazy. You thought...

1023
01:30:46,443 --> 01:30:51,312
You told Simon that people dressed like me
don't come to your part of town.

1024
01:30:52,682 --> 01:30:56,345
- You had him record the conversation?
- He told me about it.

1025
01:30:58,121 --> 01:31:01,682
You were testing me to see if I'd explode.

1026
01:31:02,492 --> 01:31:03,652
Yeah?

1027
01:31:04,694 --> 01:31:07,993
- And you refused to let that happen.
- Yeah. Not in front of Simon.

1028
01:31:08,731 --> 01:31:12,292
And if Simon wasn't there,
would you have beaten me?

1029
01:31:12,368 --> 01:31:15,963
- Like you attacked that man today?
- He was going to vomit on us.

1030
01:31:18,908 --> 01:31:22,571
What if I did that now?

1031
01:31:23,613 --> 01:31:25,740
Hey. Stop it.

1032
01:31:30,587 --> 01:31:33,021
Do you think I would do that?

1033
01:31:33,089 --> 01:31:37,458
- Vomit on my own rug to prove a point?
- I'm not sure.

1034
01:31:38,261 --> 01:31:41,025
You must think I'm capable of anything.

1035
01:31:42,332 --> 01:31:45,096
Isn't it best to stay away
from people like me?

1036
01:31:48,972 --> 01:31:50,132
Maybe.

1037
01:31:51,207 --> 01:31:54,370
Except people like me are everywhere,

1038
01:31:55,144 --> 01:31:57,908
people who are capable of anything,

1039
01:31:58,414 --> 01:32:02,851
capable of seeking justice, seeking revenge.

1040
01:32:03,620 --> 01:32:07,784
- For what?
- I lost my entire family in Lebanon.

1041
01:32:08,291 --> 01:32:13,319
One day I came back home from school
and they were wiped out, just like that.

1042
01:32:18,301 --> 01:32:20,166
Sami was my salvation.

1043
01:32:22,338 --> 01:32:26,365
He provided me
with something I could believe in.

1044
01:32:29,913 --> 01:32:32,507
I don't know what you expect from us.

1045
01:32:36,019 --> 01:32:38,852
I would like to be a part of Simon's life.

1046
01:32:41,991 --> 01:32:43,049
Why?

1047
01:32:44,227 --> 01:32:45,819
He's all I have.

1048
01:32:48,765 --> 01:32:51,825
I was never upset at my husband
for leaving me.

1049
01:32:52,936 --> 01:32:54,699
I can't explain why.

1050
01:32:56,172 --> 01:32:58,606
Your sister was from such a different world,

1051
01:32:58,675 --> 01:33:00,666
and she gave him a child.

1052
01:33:01,978 --> 01:33:03,741
Sami wanted a child.

1053
01:33:14,390 --> 01:33:17,723
You're going to have to pay for the ticket.
The tow was free.

1054
01:33:34,043 --> 01:33:35,271
<i>Grandpa.</i>

1055
01:33:36,012 --> 01:33:39,311
<i>I really need to know
what happened that night.</i>

1056
01:33:39,716 --> 01:33:41,911
<i>He was going to kill her.</i>

1057
01:33:44,020 --> 01:33:47,683
<i>- He called and said...
- He could have called to apologize</i>

1058
01:33:47,757 --> 01:33:51,420
<i>or to find out if I was back.
It could have been my mother calling.</i>

1059
01:33:55,665 --> 01:33:58,429
<i>You have to believe me, Simon.</i>

1060
01:34:00,203 --> 01:34:02,364
<i>Your father was a killer.</i>

1061
01:35:04,867 --> 01:35:07,859
Why didn't you tell me about this before?

1062
01:35:11,741 --> 01:35:14,733
I didn't think it was appropriate.

1063
01:35:16,412 --> 01:35:18,073
Yeah, good call.

1064
01:35:20,416 --> 01:35:22,111
He looked happy.

1065
01:35:24,454 --> 01:35:25,648
He was.

1066
01:35:26,756 --> 01:35:28,246
We were happy.

1067
01:35:30,159 --> 01:35:32,059
And then what happened?

1068
01:35:33,996 --> 01:35:35,793
Then he met your mom.

1069
01:35:37,300 --> 01:35:38,824
You let him go.

1070
01:35:39,335 --> 01:35:40,359
No.

1071
01:35:41,738 --> 01:35:43,467
I never let him go.

